UID:ad28f885-58cf-4441-b8e1-39ad5e172585
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/London:20260324T080000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/London:20260324T093000
SUMMARY:Block 1: NeetCode Algorithms (Foundation)
DESCRIPTION:[Phase: Foundation | Week 2 | Day 2]\n\nEasy tier. 2-3 problems. No AI\, no autocomplete\, no copilot.\n\nTalk through your approach out loud as you solve.\nTarget: 10-15 min per problem.\nIf finished early\, do one more.\nIf stuck after 15 min\, read the NeetCode video solution\, understand it\, then solve it again from scratch tomorrow.\n\nFocus areas: arrays\, hash maps\, two pointers\, stacks.\n\nRULE: No AI. No autocomplete. No copilot.\nIf you reach for a tool\, that is the muscle atrophying. Stay with it.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:cbb70e23-1ef2-41fb-aacf-b3cb48e57eb4
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/London:20260324T100000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/London:20260324T113000
SUMMARY:Block 2: Codecrafters - Build-your-own Redis
DESCRIPTION:[Phase: Foundation | Week 2 | Day 2]\n\nCodecrafters: Build-your-own Redis.\n\nWork through stages sequentially. No AI. No copilot.\nFocus on understanding the protocol\, data structures\, persistence.\nThis rebuilds manual coding stamina and gives you a real system to discuss in design interviews.\n\nKey concepts: TCP server\, RESP protocol parsing\, hash maps\, key expiry/TTL\, persistence (RDB snapshots).\n\nRULE: No AI. No copilot. Read the docs. Read the error messages.\nEvery stage you complete by hand rebuilds the muscle.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3be6cf14-00e3-40f6-b73c-e0234c6d4e0b
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/London:20260324T120000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/London:20260324T133000
SUMMARY:Block 3: System Design (Foundation)
DESCRIPTION:[Phase: Foundation | Week 2 | Day 2]\n\nNeetCode System Design: caching\, CDNs\, hashing\, databases (SQL vs NoSQL)\n\nMon-Wed: Watch NeetCode videos\, take notes BY HAND in notebook.\nThu-Fri: Practice designing systems out loud\, draw on paper.\n\nKey skill: drive the conversation. Ask clarifying questions.\nMake trade-offs explicit. Draw while talking.\n\nRULE: No AI. Paper and pen for diagrams.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:9b4af6c1-6a74-419f-99d6-6a62809fe3df
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/London:20260324T143000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/London:20260324T160000
SUMMARY:Block 4: Explain Codecrafters Out Loud
DESCRIPTION:[Phase: Foundation | Week 2 | Day 2]\n\nTake the Codecrafters stages you completed this week.\nStand up. Draw the architecture on paper or whiteboard.\nExplain what each component does and why\, as if to an interviewer.\nTime yourself - aim for 10 min per subsystem.\nPractice the phrase: 'I chose X because Y\, the trade-off is Z.'\n\nAfter this block\, you are DONE for the day.\n16:00-18:00 is leisure. No code. No study.
END:VEVENT
