UID:41a13bfe-718b-497b-b2c6-639218ceaa83
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/London:20260410T100000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/London:20260410T113000
SUMMARY:Block 2: Codecrafters - Build-your-own HTTP Server
DESCRIPTION:[Phase: Ramp | Week 4 | Day 5]\n\nCodecrafters: Build-your-own HTTP Server.\n\nRequest parsing\, routing\, concurrent connections\, compression.\nNo AI. No copilot.\nThis is foundational for any web engineering role.\n\nKey concepts: TCP sockets\, HTTP/1.1 parsing\, content negotiation\, gzip compression\, concurrent request handling.\n\nRULE: No AI. No copilot. Read the docs. Read the error messages.\nEvery stage you complete by hand rebuilds the muscle.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:6eb7a9aa-0f7f-4e49-9813-924bf5a7b327
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/London:20260410T120000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/London:20260410T133000
SUMMARY:Block 3: System Design (Ramp)
DESCRIPTION:[Phase: Ramp | Week 4 | Day 5]\n\nNeetCode System Design: design URL shortener\, design pastebin\, design Twitter feed\n\nMon-Wed: Watch NeetCode videos\, take notes BY HAND in notebook.\nThu-Fri: Practice designing systems out loud\, draw on paper.\n\nKey skill: drive the conversation. Ask clarifying questions.\nMake trade-offs explicit. Draw while talking.\n\nRULE: No AI. Paper and pen for diagrams.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:3dc6b05b-728f-499a-8a86-2c82c93a96b6
DTSTART;TZID=Europe/London:20260410T143000
DTEND;TZID=Europe/London:20260410T160000
SUMMARY:Block 4: Week Review + Plan
DESCRIPTION:[Phase: Ramp | Week 4 | Day 5]\n\nReview the week honestly.\n\n- How many NeetCode problems solved? Which patterns are strong/weak?\n- Codecrafters: how many stages completed? Anything blocked?\n- System design: can you draw and explain this week's topics cold?\n- What was the hardest moment this week? What would you do differently?\n\nWrite 3-5 bullet points in a notebook. Not for anyone else - for you.\nPlan next week: which NeetCode patterns to focus on\, which Codecrafters stages to target.\n\nThen stop. You are done for the week.\n\nAfter this block\, you are DONE for the day.\n16:00-18:00 is leisure. No code. No study.
END:VEVENT
